cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes an online object-level SLAM system that uses Mask-RCNN instance segmentation to initialise compact per-object Truncated Signed Distance Function (TSDF) reconstructions. The system also carries semantic information and existence probability for each object. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed system can be used for tracking, relocalisation and loop closure detection, which are important tasks in robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The system uses Mask-RCNN instance segmentation to initialise object reconstructions, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The system carries semantic information and existence probability for each object, which are related to artificial intelligence. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The system builds a persistent and accurate 3D graph map of arbitrary reconstructed objects, which is related to computer graphics.
